                <div class="home-content">
                    <h1>Santanu Soe</h1>
                    
                    <div class="intro-text">
<p>
  I am a 
  <a href="https://pmrf.in/" target="_blank" class="highlight">Prime Minister's Research Fellow (PMRF)</a> 
  and 
  <a href="https://www.iitm.ac.in/academics/joint-phd-programmes" target="_blank" class="highlight">Joint PhD scholar</a> 
  in the <span class="highlight">Department of Mathematics</span> at 
  <a href="https://www.iitm.ac.in/" target="_blank" class="highlight">IIT Madras</a> 
  and the <span class="highlight">School of Mathematics and Statistics</span> at the 
  <a href="https://www.unimelb.edu.au/" target="_blank" class="highlight">University of Melbourne</a>, 
  working under the supervision of 
  <a href="https://home.iitm.ac.in/vetri/home.html" target="_blank" class="highlight">V. Vetrivel</a> 
  and 
  <a href="https://matthewktam.com/" target="_blank" class="highlight">Matthew K. Tam</a>. 
  I have also received the
  <a href="https://scholarships.unimelb.edu.au/awards/melbourne-research-scholarship" target="_blank" class="highlight">
    Melbourne Research Scholarship
  </a> 
  for my doctoral studies at Unimelb.
</p>

<p>
  My research focuses on designing and analysing algorithms that are both theoretically sound and computationally efficient. 
  I am particularly interested in 
  <span class="highlight">operator splitting methods</span>, 
  <span class="highlight">primal-dual algorithms</span>, and 
  <span class="highlight">monotone inclusion problems</span>.
</p>
                        
                    </div>
                    
